URL = http://aflfnorthcoast2005.wikispaces.com/theory

 
'''The (Open) Networked Learning Model'''


"The idea that a learning environment can be constructed using a collection of freely available online tools (instead of an integrated suite or LMS).

Utilising a plethora of rich media content that is open and freely available and shared - open source, open content, Creative Commons.

"Distributed Knowledge"

* No central repository - drawn from sources all over the web (often still in their original context).
* No central authoritative source.
* Dynamic - constantly changing and being updated."
(http://aflfnorthcoast2005.wikispaces.com/theory)

